Subject: specifically dependent continuant
Value: b is a relational specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a specifically dependent continuant and there are n > 1 independent continuants c1, … cn which are not spatial regions are such that for all 1  i < j  n, ci  and cj share no common parts, are such that for each 1  i  n, b s-depends_on ci at every time t during the course of b’s existence (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [131-004])@en

Subject: specifically dependent continuant
Value: b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of b’s existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])@en

Subject: has_qualifying_environment
Value: A relation used to describe  an environment contextualizing the identity of an entity.

Subject: microsatellite alteration
Value: A relation used to describe  an environment contextualizing the identity of an entity.

Subject: has_qualifying_process
Value: A relation used to describe  a process contextualizing the identity of an entity.

Subject: repeat region alteration
Value: A relation used to describe  a process contextualizing the identity of an entity.

Subject: intrinsic genotype
Value: A genotype that describes the total variation in heritable genomic sequence of a cell or organism, typically in terms of alterations from some reference or background genotype.

Subject: genomic genotype
Value: A genotype that describes the total variation in heritable genomic sequence of a cell or organism, typically in terms of alterations from some reference or background genotype.

Subject: obsolete_approximates_sequence
Value: Created subproperties 'approximates_sequence' and 'resolves to sequence'. Genotypes and other sequence variant artifacts are not always expected to completely specify a sequence, but rather provide some approximation based on available knowledge. The 'resolves_to_sequence' property can be used when the sequence variant artifact is able to completely resolve a sequence, and the 'approximates_sequence' property can be used when it does not.

Subject: obsolete_resolves_to_sequence
Value: Created subproperties 'approximates_sequence' and 'resolves to sequence'. Genotypes and other sequence variant artifacts are not always expected to completely specify a sequence, but rather provide some approximation based on available knowledge. The 'resolves_to_sequence' property can be used when the sequence variant artifact is able to completely resolve a sequence, and the 'approximates_sequence' property can be used when it does not.

Subject: chromosome band
Value: http://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/handbook/howgeneswork/genelocation and http://people.rit.edu/rhrsbi/GeneticsPages/Handouts/ChromosomeNomenclature.pdf, both of which define the nomenclature for the banding hierarchy we use here:chromosome > arm > region > band > sub-bandNote that an alternate nomenclature for this hierarchy is here (http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Class/MLACourse/Original8Hour/Genetics/chrombanding.html):chromosome > arm > band > sub-band > sub-sub-band

Subject: obsolete sequence feature collection
Value: perhaps not same as SO:sequence collection, as here we explicitly include features that can have an extent of zero (and SO:sequence collection is a collection of regions that have an extent of at least one)

Subject: variant genome
Value: SO:0001506 ! variant_genome (definition of SO term here is too vague to know if has same meaning as GENO class here)

Subject: independent continuant
Value: b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])@en

Subject: process
Value: p is a process = Def. p is an occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [083-003])@en

Subject: disposition
Value: b is a disposition means: b is a realizable entity & b’s bearer is some material entity & b is such that if it ceases to exist, then its bearer is physically changed, & b’s realization occurs when and because this bearer is in some special physical circumstances, & this realization occurs in virtue of the bearer’s physical make-up. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [062-002])@en

Subject: quality
Value: a quality is a specifically dependent continuant that, in contrast to roles and dispositions, does not require any further process in order to be realized. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [055-001])@en

Subject: specifically dependent continuant
Value: b is a relational specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a specifically dependent continuant and there are n > 1 independent continuants c1, … cn which are not spatial regions are such that for all 1  i < j  n, ci  and cj share no common parts, are such that for each 1  i  n, b s-depends_on ci at every time t during the course of b’s existence (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [131-004])@en

Subject: specifically dependent continuant
Value: b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of b’s existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])@en

Subject: role
Value: b is a role means: b is a realizable entity and b exists because there is some single bearer that is in some special physical, social, or institutional set of circumstances in which this bearer does not have to be and b is not such that, if it ceases to exist, then the physical make-up of the bearer is thereby changed. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [061-001])@en

Subject: generically dependent continuant
Value: b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])@en

Subject: obsolete sequence feature collection
Value: a collection more than one sequence features (ie a collection of discontinuous sequence features)

Subject: human population
Value: a population of homo sapiens grouped together in virtue of their sharing some commonality (either an inherent attribute or an externally assigned role)

Subject: obsolete sequence feature collection attribute
Value: sequence attribute that can inhere only in a collection of more than one sequence features

Subject: obsolete dominant inheritance
Value: disposition inhering in a genetic locus variant that is realized in its inheritance by some offspring such that at least a partial variant-associated phenotype is apparent in heterozygotes

Subject: obsolete_is_phenotype_of_genotype
Value: shortcut relation used to link a phenotype directly to a genotype of an organism

Subject: aneusomic
Value: a sequence attribute of a chromosome or chromosomal region that has been abnormally duplicated or lost, as the result of a non-disjunction event or unbalanced translocation.

Subject: homoplasmic
Value: an allelic state where a single allele exists at a particular location in the organellar genome (mitochondrial or plastid) of a cell/organism.

Subject: heteroplasmic
Value: an allelic state where more than one type of allele exists at a particular location in the organellar genome (mitochondrial or plastid) of a cell/organism.

Subject: has_zygosity
Value: a relation to link a single locus complement to its zygosity.

Subject: is_targeted_by
Value: relation between an molecular agent and its molecular target

Subject: obsolete gametic
Value: a quality inhering in a feature in virtue of its presence only in the genome of gametes (germ cells).

Subject: information content entity
Value: an information content entity is an entity that is generically dependent on some artifact and stands in relation of aboutness to some entity@en

Subject: is about
Value: is_about is a (currently) primitive relation that relates an information artifact to an entity.

Subject: population
Value: a population is a collection of individuals from the same taxonomic class living, counted or sampled at a particular site or in a particular area

Subject: inheres_in
Value: a relation between a specifically dependent continuant (the dependent) and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the dependent specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

Subject: bearer of
Value: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a specifically dependent continuant (the dependent), in which the dependent specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

Subject: participates in
Value: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

Subject: has participant
Value: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

Subject: has quality
Value: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a quality, in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

Subject: has disposition
Value: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a disposition, in which the disposition specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

Subject: overlaps
Value: x overlaps y if and only if there exists some z such that x has part z and z part of y

Subject: in taxon
Value: x is in taxon y if an only if y is an organism, and the relationship between x and y is one of: part of (reflexive), developmentally preceded by, derives from, secreted by, expressed.

Subject: has input
Value: p has direct input c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

Subject: has output
Value: p has output c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present at the beginning of p.

Subject: has member
Value: has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.

Subject: bounds sequence of
Value: x bounds the sequence of y iff the upstream-most part of x is upstream of or coincident with the upstream-most part of y, and the downstream-most part of x is downstream of or coincident with the downstream-most part of y

Subject: has subsequence
Value: x has subsequence y iff all of the sequence parts of x are sequence parts of y

Subject: overlaps sequence of
Value: x overlaps the sequence of x if and only if x has a subsequence z and z is a subsequence of y.

Subject: is upstream of sequence of
Value: inverse of downstream of sequence of

Subject: is downstream of sequence of
Value: x is downstream of the sequence of y iff either (1) x and y have sequence units, and all units of x are downstream of all units of y, or (2) x and y are sequence units, and x is either immediately downstream of y, or transitively downstream of y.
